p:
Laurel (
 Laurus nobilis L.) fam. Lauraceae is a shrub native to the Mediterranean region and cultivated in a number of countries in Asia, Europe, and the Americas as a spice, or used as ornamental plant (
 Parthasarathy et al., 2008). Laurel leaves, also known as bay leaves, are a major spice, which has been used traditionally as an ingredient for improving food flavor and taste. Naturally occurring biologically active compounds in leaves include terpenes, terpene derivates, polyphenols, alkaloids, minerals, vitamins (
 Caputo et al., 2017; 
 Chahal et al., 2017; 
 Parthasarathy et al., 2008).
